cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.EM, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of neural networks with the back-propagation learning algorithm. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper proposes the use of memristor cross-bar matrices for weight storage, which is an emerging technology in the field of hardware implementation of neural networks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the hardware implementation of neural networks. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetism) is a less likely category, but it is mentioned in the abstract as one of the problems that need to be solved in the proposed approach. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a less likely category, but it is possible as the paper discusses the recognition operations of the neural network.
